 :sidecar: n. 1. Syn. {slap on the side}. Esp. used of add-ons for the late
and unlamented IBM PCjr. 2. The IBM PC compatibility box that could be bolted
onto the side of an Amiga. Designed and produced by Commodore, it broke all
of the company's own design rules. If it worked with any other peripherals,
it was by {magic}. 3. More generally, any of various devices designed to be
connected to the expansion slot on the left side of the Amiga 500 (and later,
600 & 1200), which included a hard drive controller, a hard drive, and
additional memory.